n for your thought process, than a physical relationship.\n\n- Rajasaraswathii, Success-Talks : For Evolution of Your Success\n|\nI had thought that words were instruments of precision. Now I know that they devour the world, leaving nothing in its place.\n\n- Steven Millhauser, Dangerous Laughter\n|\nI want to think again of dangerous and noble things. I want to be light and frolicsome. I want to be improbable beautiful and afraid of nothing, as though I had wings.\n\n- Mary Oliver, Owls and Other Fantasies: Poems and Essays\n|\nPassion will warm you for days, infatuation will warm you for months, but love will set you on fire for a lifetime.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nPursue knowledge as though it is your life-blood, then you will know greatness!\n\n- Monique\n|\nGod will bring the right person into your life at the right time. Always believe that! If they are not there, God isn't finished yet!\n\n- Shannon\n|\nInto the wind we vary,Our hearts free of youth,Mold me into envy,If I can’t have your muse;Under toe,Walk to the throne,After centuries of life.\n\n- Adrianna\n|\nLights,' I said softly. This had become my favorite word over the past week. In my mind, it had become synonymous with freedom.\n\n- Ernest Cline, Ready Player One\n|\nTo realize the truth, you have to cross the boundaries of all religions and prophets.\n\n- Amit Ray, Meditation: Insights and Inspirations\n|\nHappiness doesn't result from what we get, but from what we give.\n\n- Ben\n|\nTruth and facts are woven together. However, sometimes facts can blind you from seeing what is actually going on in someone’s life.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nThe more you read, the more you want to know, and so the more questions you have.\n\n- Xinran, Miss Chopsticks\n|\nSelf under self, a pile of selves I standThreaded on time, and with metaphysic handLift the farm like a lid and seeFarm within farm, and in the centre, me.\n\n- Norman MacCaig, The Poems of Norman MacCaig\n|\nMy former identity was lying around, somewhere, fragmented and buried, like shards from an earlier civilization.\n\n- Laurie Nadel, Dancing with the Wind: A True Story of Zen in the Art of Windsurfing\n|\nI’m not going to tear you down… If you’re bad-mouthing me, you’re already down.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Unapologetically You: Reflections on Life and the Human Experience\n|\nHow freeing of a thought: instead of worrying about leaving a legacy, to leave no trace of one's existence. How liberating indeed!\n\n- Kamand\n|\nSometimes when we find love we pretend it away, or ignore it, or tell ourselves we're imagining it. Because it's the most painful kind of hope there is. By indifference . By death.\n\n- Leigh\n|\nI always wanted to know what it is right. Maybe we know each other from time immemorial, if you know that in you is the eternal energy of goodness, which is most important for you.\n\n- Gregor\n|\nEach man follows his own path - his own destiny, if you will. And only he is responsible for the choice.\n\n- Heather Graham, Night Moves\n|\nNever apologize for showing feeling. When you do so, you apologize for the truth.\n\n- Benjamin\n|\nWriters seldom choose as friends those self-centered characters who are never in trouble, never make mistakes, and always count their change as it is handed to them.\n\n- Catherine\n|\nNothing in this world is difficult, but thinking makes it seem so. Where there is true will, there is always a way.\n\n- Wu Cheng'en, Monkey: A Journey to the West\n|\nFind someone who has a life that you want and figure out how they got it. Read books, pick your role models wisely. Find out what they did and do it.\n\n- Lana\n|\nUnderstand one thing very clearly. Because all this: your time, this world, your life in it and all of those opportunities, they have a deadline.\n\n- Jellis\n|\nKnowing how to be solitary is central to the art of loving. When we can be alone, we can be with others without using them as a means of escape.\n\n- bell\n|\n[Poetry] was a form of incantation, a means of welding the world inside his head to the one that surrounded him, words the fiery chain that bound it all together.\n\n- Elizabeth Hand, Radiant Days\n|\nThe plain truth can be the hardest thing to see when it's about yourself. If you don't want to know the truth, you'll do anything to disguise it.\n\n- Sara Pennypacker, Pax\n|\nEndeavor to live a simple life, but filled with complex love.\n\n- Auliq-Ice\n|\nWhen you come to the edge of all that you know, you must believe one of two things: either there will be ground to stand on, or you will be given wings to fly.\n\n- O.R. Melling, The Summer King\n|\nIt is a fact of life that when you are small, people expect little things from you. But when you've done a great thing, people are amazed.\n\n- Ymatruz\n|\nThe truth is not distorted here, but rather a distortion is used to get at truth.\n\n- Flannery\n|\nLove, the poet said, is woman's whole existence.\n\n- Virginia Woolf, Orlando\n|\nAnd then Luke had appeared, like a gust that had come to teach me that in life, there was nothing more precious than life itself.\n\n- Liz Thebart, Walk Away\n|\nRight now, just speak gently your words of wisdom to the youngsters.Sooner or later, those words will arrive at the right place in their hearts.\n\n- Toba Beta, My Ancestor Was an Ancient Astronaut\n|\nWhat we think & how we think plays a major role in creating the life we live. If you want to change your life, change the way you look at things around.\n\n- Taranpreet\n|\nLove is as we will it to be.' ~ Amunhotep El Bey\n\n- Amunhotep El Bey, The Quotations Book of life and Death\n|\nNot only can you decide to be great, you also have the power to determine the height of your greatness.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nFor us to regard others as worthy, we have to begin by regarding ourselves as worthy.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Boost Your Self Esteem\n|\nTeaching mathematics, like teaching any art, requires the ability to inspire the student. Inspiration requires marketing, 